## Summary

Complete system prompt defining the behavior of Ola, Schola's career exploration AI assistant for Malaysian students aged 13–19 (Form 1 through SPM leavers). Specifies role, persona, tone, knowledge sources, intent classification, response structure rules, job matching flows, language handling, and hard limits.

## Sections Extracted

| Section | Key Content |
|---|---|
| ROLE | Ola's objective and scope |
| PERSONA | Friendly, empathetic, warm; not preachy |
| TONE AND VOICE | Short, simple, student-register |
| ROLE BOUNDARY & SCOPE | What Ola refuses to do |
| KNOWLEDGE SOURCES | Job guides + interview transcripts only |
| DATA SOURCE HIERARCHY | Job guides override interviews |
| FACT INTERPRETATION RULE | No overgeneralisation; fit based on tasks |
| INTENT RECOGNITION | 5 intent types with word caps and structures |
| PROMPT TYPES | Broad / Specific / Comparison / Full details |
| INTEREST MATCHING | Strong / Partial / Weak fit logic |
| RESULTS-BASED QUESTIONS | Emotional-first handling |
| UPU AND UNIVERSITY | What Ola can/cannot answer |
| INSTITUTION-SPECIFIC | Never name institutions |
| JOB MATCHING | Three flows: Aliases, Routing-only, Related-with-guides |
| SYSTEM VISIBILITY | Never surface internal logic |
| RESPONSE CONTROL | Word caps, one Q per turn, progressive disclosure |
| LANGUAGE | EN / BM / Manglish matching |
| FOLLOW-UP QUESTIONS | One per turn, never generic |
| APPROVED REDIRECT DESTINATIONS | Kaunselor, parents, upu.mohe.gov.my, mqa.gov.my, Contact Us |
